## 🚀 Installation & Setup

### 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-org/emonado.git
cd emonado
```

### 2. Install PHP Dependencies

```bash
composer install
```

### 3. Configure Environment Variables

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Open `.env` and fill in the required values:

```env
# Database
DATABASE_URL="mysql://root:@127.0.0.1:3307/emonado_db?serverVersion=mariadb-10.4.32&charset=utf8mb4"

# Mailer (Gmail SMTP)
MAILER_DSN=gmail+smtp://your_email@gmail.com:your_app_password@default
MAILER_FROM=your_email@gmail.com

# AI APIs
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key
GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key_here

# SMS (Mailjet)
MAILJET_API_KEY=your_mailjet_api_key
MAILJET_SECRET_KEY=your_mailjet_secret_key

# Spotify (Music Therapy)
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=your_spotify_client_id
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET=your_spotify_client_secret

# PDF (wkhtmltopdf path — adjust for your OS)
WKHTMLTOPDF_PATH=C:/Progra~1/wkhtmltopdf/bin/wkhtmltopdf.exe  # Windows
# WKHTMLTOPDF_PATH=/usr/local/bin/wkhtmltopdf                  # Linux/macOS
```

### 4. Start the Database

**Option A — Docker (recommended):**
```bash
docker compose up -d
```

**Option B — Local MySQL/MariaDB:**
Ensure your MySQL server is running and the credentials in `.env` match your local setup.

### 5. Set Up the Database Schema

```bash
# Run migrations
php bin/console doctrine:migrations:migrate

# Or, for a fresh schema sync (development only)
php bin/console doctrine:schema:update --force
```

### 6. Load Default Users (optional)

```bash
php bin/console app:create-default-users
```

This creates demo accounts for each role (admin, psychologue, patient).

### 7. Install Frontend Assets

```bash
php bin/console importmap:install
php bin/console assets:install
```

### 8. Start the Development Server

```bash
symfony server:start
# or
php -S 127.0.0.1:8080 -t public/
```

Then open your browser at: **http://127.0.0.1:8080**

> **Windows users:** You can also double-click `start-server.bat` to launch the server automatically.

